Description

Formula: g(x,y) = f(x,y) + η(x,y), where η follows Maxwell-Boltzmann distribution

Mathematical Formula

\[g(x,y) = f(x,y) + \eta(x,y), where \eta follows Maxwell-Boltzmann distribution\]

This noise affects the image according to the formula shown above.

Implementation

def add_maxwell_noise(image, scale=25):
    """
    Formula: g(x,y) = f(x,y) + η(x,y), where η follows Maxwell-Boltzmann distribution
    p(z) = sqrt(2/π)*(z²/a³)*e^(-z²/(2a²)) for z ≥ 0
    """
    row, col = image.shape
    noise = stats.maxwell.rvs(scale=scale, size=(row, col))
    noise -= np.mean(noise)  # Center the noise around zero
    noisy_img = image + noise
    return np.clip(noisy_img, 0, 255).astype(np.uint8), noise

Applications

  • Image processing and filtering techniques
  • Realistic texture generation in computer graphics
  • Testing and validating denoising algorithms
  • Simulation of real-world imaging conditions
